description: From Latin octodecim (“eighteen”)  +‎ -illion; compare tredecillion, quattuordecillion, etc.

entries.meaning: (US, modern British and Australian, short scale, rare) 1057.
examples: The reason is that the rays created in the core are softened on their outward journey by being handled by the octodecillion-odd atoms of gas outside the core that are part of the sun but play no part in the central fusions.

entries.meaning: (dated British and Australian, long scale, rare) 10108.
